    <string name="character_name_elias">Elias Thorne</string>
    <string name="character_description_text">"Knowledge is the only currency that doesn\'t depreciate." Elias has spent forty years documenting the lost dialects of the northern peaks. He speaks with a rhythmic precision that feels like reading a classic novel.</string>
    <string name="environment_description_text">A dimly lit study in the Archive of Silence. The air smells of old parchment and cedarwood. Dust motes dance in the single beam of sunlight cutting through the heavy velvet curtains.</string>
    <string name="character_description_sample">Elias是一位深居简出的古董书籍修复师。他说话谨慎，总是带着一种淡淡的、近乎忧郁的从容。他对18世纪的装帧工艺有着近乎执着的迷恋。</string>
    <string name="environment_sample">一间位于雾气弥漫的小巷尽头的书店。室内充满了皮革、陈旧纸张和蜂蜡的气味。窗外是永恒的黄昏。</string>

